# Template — copy the KEY names; values are set via dotenvx (encrypted).
#
# Do NOT put real secrets here. To set the real (encrypted) value, use the same
# codified flow as ../earlbear-domain:
#   make collect-secret VARS=CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN   # seeds a placeholder in .env, opens it
#   # paste the value next to CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=, then:
#   make encrypt        # plaintext → dotenvx ciphertext (safe to commit)
#   make key-backup     # back the private key (.env.keys) up to LastPass (survives a fresh clone)
#
# To run a command with the decrypted env (this is how deploy:internal auths):
#   ./node_modules/.bin/dotenvx run -- wrangler pages deploy ...

# Cloudflare scoped API token: Account → Cloudflare Pages → Edit (earlbear account).
# Used ONLY by `make deploy-internal` (npm run deploy:internal) to `wrangler pages
# deploy` the INTERNAL blog build to the earlbear-blog-internal Pages project.
# This is the auth model the earlbear-domain deploy-contract audit requires
# (`make -C ../earlbear-domain audit-deploy`) — a scoped, dotenvx-encrypted token,
# NOT machine wrangler OAuth. Scope it to Pages:Edit only (least privilege).
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
